<sect2><title>Docbook-scripts</title>
<para>
<command>Docbook-scripts</command> is a series of simple scripts which make it easier to implement the Docbook documentation for the project. The scripts are written in a variety of shell and perl, and need to be included in your current path to be used.
</para>

<sect3><title>Authors</title>
<para>
The scripts were developed by Michael Still (mikal@stillhq.com) for a separate project earlier this year. They are available for download from http://www.stillhq.com
</para>
</sect3>

<sect3><title>Installation</title>
<para>
Simply extract the tarball, and add the resultant directory to your path.
</para>
</sect3>
</sect2>